enhancer.options.keywordProperty.label: Property value used during enhancement
enhancer.options.keywordProperty.descrip: Generally, this enhancer will use file/folder name of resource to perform enhancement and its not necessary to change this.
enhancer.options.keywordProperty.tip: In some cases, you can change the property value used during enhancement to perform enhancement on other property values.
enhancer.options.propertyValueScope.desc: Property value scope usually means who the property value is generated by.
enhancer.options.propertyValueScope.tip: For internal options, property value scope will be ignored.
enhancer.options.manualScope.title: Manual property value scope has been selected
enhancer.options.manualScope.description: Manual property value scope means the property values are generated by yourself, and these values are typically not yet available at the time of enhancement.
enhancer.options.pretreat.label: Pretreat property value
enhancer.options.pretreat.description: If checked, the property value will be pretreated before enhancement.
enhancer.options.pretreat.tip: You can configure the special texts to be pretreated in special text page under data menu.
enhancer.options.configure.title: Configure enhancer
enhancer.options.runAfter.label: Run after enhancers
enhancer.options.runAfter.description: You can perform chained enhancement by customizing the execution order of the enhancers.
enhancer.options.runAfter.tip: Generally, you can just leave it as empty.
enhancer.options.enhanceProperties.label: Dynamic Property Configuration
enhancer.options.enhanceProperties.tip: Configure dynamic properties for this enhancer. Static properties are managed in the external property list.
enhancer.categoryOptions.title: Configure enhancer:{{enhancerName}} for category:{{categoryName}}
enhancer.regex.captureGroups.label: Available capture groups:
enhancer.regex.captureGroups.warning: No named capture groups were found, so the enhancement will not take effect.
enhancer.regex.expressions.description: You can set multiple regex expressions(separated by new line) to match the file or folder name of each resource.
enhancer.regex.captureGroups.mergeDescri: Text matched by multiple capture groups with the same name will be merged into a list and deduplicated.
enhancer.regex.expressions.categoryTip: After setting regex expressions, you must go to category page to configure regex enhancer for each category.
enhancer.regex.expressions.namingTip: You need to use the same name(index-based group name will be ignored) as the capture group for the dynamic enhancement target, otherwise the resource may not be enhanced.
enhancer.regex.expressions.label: Regex expressions

enhancer.target.saveAsProperty.label: Save as property
enhancer.target.otherOptions.label: Other options
enhancer.target.default.label: Default
enhancer.target.noProperty.warning: Target will not be applied because there is no property to store it.
enhancer.target.label: Target
enhancer.target.dynamicLabel.tip: This is not a fixed enhancement target, which will be replaced with other content when data is collected
enhancer.target.configured.label: Configured
enhancer.target.bindProperty.label: Bind property
enhancer.targetOptions.autoMatch.label: Auto match on empty values
enhancer.targetOptions.autoMatch.descrip: By default, an empty layer will be created if we meet an empty value in multilevel data.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoMatch.checked: If checked, this kind of data will be matched with the most similar multilevel value in the database.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoMatch.example: For example, assume we already have a multilevel data: a->b->c, then for the incoming data: ->->c, the values of 1st and 2nd layers of which are empty.
If this option is checked, we'll save ->->c as a->b->c, otherwise the incoming value ->->c will be saved.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoMatch.warning: This option may cause unexpected behaviors, make sure you have enough confidence to merge the produced data into data in db before check it.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoBind.label: Auto bind property
enhancer.targetOptions.autoBind.descript: If this option is checked, a property with the same name and type of the target will be bound automatically.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoBind.createTi: If there isn't such a property, a new property will be created and bound to this target.
enhancer.targetOptions.autoBind.dynamicT: If this option is checked in default options of a dynamic target, all unlisted dynamic targets will be bound to properties of the same type with the same name.
This property is not bound to the category, its data will not be displayed.
enhancer.tip.partialSetup.warning: Some of targets are not mapped to a property, corresponding data will not be enhanced.
enhancer.tip.noSetup.warning: None of targets is mapped to a property, so no data will be enhanced.

enhancer.records.noProfilesFound.warning: No resource profiles found with this enhancer configured
enhancer.records.selectProfile.label: Select resource profile
enhancer.records.noProfiles.title: No resource profiles configured for this enhancer
enhancer.records.noProfiles.description: Please configure a resource profile with {{enhancerName}} enhancer to enable data retrieval
enhancer.records.noData.title: No enhancement data available yet
enhancer.records.noData.description: Enhancement data will be generated automatically in the background, or you can click the button above to trigger it manually
enhancer.records.resourcePath.label: Path of resource
enhancer.records.noEnhancers.title: No enhancers configured
enhancer.records.noEnhancers.description: This resource has no enhancement records yet. Please configure enhancers in resource profiles to enable automatic data enhancement.
enhancer.records.dataCreatedAt.label: Data created at
enhancer.records.dataCreatedAt.tip: The data has been created, indicating that the enhancer has completed the data retrieval process, which is typically done by accessing third-party sites or executing specific internal logic. You can check the status of the data retrieval in the table below. Frequent repeated data retrieval attempts may result in access denial from third-party services.
enhancer.records.dataAppliedAt.label: Data applied at
enhancer.records.dataAppliedAt.tip: The application of data indicates that the retrieved data has been successfully converted into attribute values. This step is conducted entirely within the program, without involving any third-party data exchange.
enhancer.records.enhanceProcess.tip: Retrieve data then apply data. To reduce the possibility of access denial from third-party services, it is recommended to apply data only after all data has been retrieved. Configuring enhancer options in category won't affect the data retrieval process, it only affects the data applying process.
enhancer.records.applyData.tip: Apply the data to property values of the resource.
enhancer.records.notConfigured.title: Enhancer not configured in resource profiles
enhancer.records.notConfigured.descripti: This enhancer is not currently configured in any resource profile. The data shown below is from previous enhancements. To enable automatic updates, please configure this enhancer in the resource profile settings.
